name: CerebrovascularDisease
title: Cerebrovascular Disease
description: SNOMED CT intensional (rule-based) value set for defining cerebrovascular disease diagnoses, available for a range of potential uses including problem-oriented views of relevant clinical information, clinical decision support rules, electronic patient registries, and data analytics.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Broad group of diagnosis concepts for acute and chronic cerebrovascular diseases.),(Data Element Scope: Employs SNOMED CT concept hierarchies primarily in the Disorder branch, though some can be in the Situation branch.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes disorders of intracranial and extracranial arteries of the head and neck such as arterial stenosis, thrombosis, embolism, aneurysm, or dissection. Also includes conditions such as arteriovenous malformations and lacunar strokes.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes trauma to arteries of head and neck.)
